OL,6,FData was reported from The Shelter
OL,7,FTrust, FREEDA (formerly Women's
OL,8,FRefuge), The Sanctuary Trust, and the
OL,9,Fgovernment's Housing Advice Service
OL,10,Fand released ahead of World Homeless
OL,11,FDay (Thursday 10 October).
OL,13,FFigures reveal that 204 islanders
OL,14,Fvisited homeless accommodation and
OL,15,Fservice providers 220 times between 1
OL,16,FApril and 30 June 2024.
OL,18,FOf those, fewer than five were defined
OL,19,Fas sleeping rough, with 180 islanders
OL,20,Fliving in temporary places to sleep in
OL,21,Finstitutional or shelter accommodation.
